<div class="cd cp">
  <div class="tg">Systemic Healer</div>
  <h3>BPC-157: The Tissue Repair Peptide</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Type:</strong> Systemic peptide (15 amino acids) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Origin:</strong> Isolated from gastric juices &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Routes:</strong> Subcutaneous injection, oral &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Primary Actions:</strong> Angiogenesis, fibroblast migration, anti-inflammatory, wound healing</p>
</div>

<p>BPC-157 has gained significant interest in regenerative medicine. Originally isolated from gastric juices, it has shown remarkable healing properties across multiple tissue types (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29898089/">Sikiric et al., 2018</a>).</p>

<p>It accelerates the formation of new blood vessels (angiogenesis) and promotes the migration of fibroblasts to wound sites. It also modulates the inflammatory response by reducing TNF-alpha and other pro-inflammatory cytokines.</p>

<p>For skin specifically, BPC-157 strengthens barrier integrity and accelerates healing after cosmetic procedures. It reduces scarring and improves overall tissue quality.</p>

