<!-- ========== HAIR SECTION ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>Peptides for Hair: What the Science Says</h2>

<p>Hair loss and thinning are driven by many factors: genetics, hormonal imbalances, oxidative stress, poor scalp circulation, and follicle inflammation. Peptides offer a different approach by restoring biological signaling that supports healthy follicle function.</p>

<h3>How GHK-Cu Supports Hair Growth</h3>

<p>GHK-Cu has been shown to enlarge follicle size and promote the transition of dormant follicles into active growth phases. It stimulates the Wnt signaling pathway that regulates hair cycling.</p>

<p>Research published in <em>Bioactive Materials</em> found that a microemulsion delivery system for copper peptides triggered hair follicle growth in mice within six days. This outpaced both standard copper peptide solutions and 5% minoxidil (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35415294/">Zhang et al., 2022</a>).</p>

<div class="d-p">
  <div class="s">Clinical Context</div>
  <p>GHK-Cu's advantage over minoxidil for some users is tolerability. Minoxidil causes persistent scalp irritation in a significant percentage of users, while copper peptides are generally well tolerated and can be combined with other treatments.</p>
</div>

<h3>Other Peptides for Hair</h3>

<p>BPC-157 supports hair health indirectly through its angiogenic properties. By increasing blood vessel formation around follicles, it improves nutrient delivery to the hair root.</p>

<p>Melanotan 2, while primarily known for skin pigmentation, has shown some ability to promote hair darkening and thickening through melanocortin receptor activation. However, its side effect profile makes it a less popular choice for this purpose alone.</p>

<!-- ========== SKINCARE ROUTINE ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>How to Build a Peptide Skincare Routine</h2>

<p>Peptides work best in leave-on products like serums and moisturizers, where they have prolonged contact with the skin. Apply them after cleansing and before heavier creams for best absorption.</p>

<div class="g2">
  <div class="mc">
    <h4 style="color:var(--blue);">Morning Routine</h4>
    <p><strong>1.</strong> Gentle cleanser (non-stripping)<br>
    <strong>2.</strong> Hydrating toner to prep skin<br>
    <strong>3.</strong> Peptide serum (pat gently, don't rub)<br>
    <strong>4.</strong> Moisturizer with niacinamide or hyaluronic acid<br>
    <strong>5.</strong> Sunscreen SPF 30+ (essential for collagen protection)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="mc">
    <h4 style="color:var(--teal);">Evening Routine</h4>
    <p><strong>1.</strong> Double cleanse (remove sunscreen and makeup)<br>
    <strong>2.</strong> Peptide serum (GHK-Cu works well for nighttime repair)<br>
    <strong>3.</strong> Night cream or retinol (alternate retinol nights if sensitive)<br>
    <strong>4.</strong> Optional: peptide-infused eye cream for delicate areas</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="d-a">
  <div class="s">Pairing Caution</div>
  <p><strong>Good combinations:</strong> Peptides + hyaluronic acid, peptides + niacinamide. <strong>Use caution:</strong> Copper peptides + vitamin C (instability risk), copper peptides + strong acids (AHA/BHA at high concentrations).</p>
</div>

<!-- ========== STACKING ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>How to Stack Peptides for Maximum Results</h2>

<p>Combining complementary peptides can address multiple pathways simultaneously. The key is choosing peptides that work through different mechanisms rather than duplicating the same one.</p>

<table class="tbl">
<thead><tr><th>Goal</th><th>Ideal Stack</th><th>Duration</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>Anti-aging</strong></td><td>GHK-Cu (topical) + Matrixyl serum + Argireline</td><td>8&ndash;12 weeks</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Hair regrowth</strong></td><td>GHK-Cu (scalp) + BPC-157 systemic + TB-500</td><td>12&ndash;16 weeks</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Post-procedure recovery</strong></td><td>BPC-157 + GHK-Cu (topical)</td><td>4&ndash;8 weeks</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong><a href="/articles/best-peptides-for-anti-aging">Total rejuvenation</a></strong></td><td>GHK-Cu (topical/systemic) + CJC-1295/Ipamorelin</td><td>12+ weeks</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>For anti-aging stacks, the combination of GHK-Cu with Matrixyl is especially effective. GHK-Cu handles collagen remodeling and protection while Matrixyl stimulates new collagen IV synthesis in the basement membrane.</p>

<p>For hair regrowth, adding systemic BPC-157 to topical GHK-Cu addresses both local follicle signaling and systemic blood vessel formation around the scalp.</p>

<!-- ========== TIMELINE ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>When to Expect Results</h2>

<p>Peptides work with your body's natural repair processes, which take time. Patience and consistency matter more than product concentration.</p>

<table class="tbl">
